post_text:
Registration is open for 2020 fall sports. Completed forms and fees must be submitted to begin practice. Students also must have an up-to-date physical (good for 3 years).

Cross Country practice began August 17. Other fall sports training (football, volleyball, cheerleading) will run September 14 - October 3.
- Football will practice on Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, and Friday at 4:15 p.m. - 5:45 p.m.
- Volleyball (varsity) will practice on Monday and Wednesday at 5:30 p.m. -7:30 p.m. JV & C-squad will practice Tuesday and Thursday at 3:30 p.m. - 5:30 p.m.
- Cheerleading will practice Tuesday at 7:15 p.m. - 8:30 p.m. and Wednesday and Friday at 5:30 p,m, - 7:30 p,m,

Spring sports training (Baseball, Softball, Boys and Girls Track) will run October 5-24.

post_text:
Remember, if you have a comment that you want to be read during visitor comment time at the virtual school board meeting tomorrow (Monday), please submit it before 5:00 p.m. on meeting day by sending an email to visitorcomments@wem.k12.mn.us.

Comments from visitors should be informational in nature and not exceed 3 minutes per issue. The Board will not engage in a discussion or debate but will take the information and find answers if it is appropriate. As part of the protocol, visitors must keep their ideas and opinions related to policy issues. It is unacceptable for any speaker to slander, engage in character assassination, or discuss student or personnel issues (i.e. teacher, coaches, bus drivers, principals, board members, etc.) at a public board meeting.

post_text: We know you are eager to learn about fall plans for WEM. The school board was scheduled to vote on the reopening model at the meeting tonight. Unfortunately, due to unforeseen circumstances, the meeting has been postponed to Monday, August 31 at 6:00. In the meantime, you can review the detailed Safe Return to School Plan. Schedules and teachers should be sent out by the middle of next week. Entrance conferences are September 8-11. An electronic sign-up sheet will be emailed out this week. Classes will begin on September 14. Please direct questions to Deb at the Elementary office 507-362-4439 or Becky at the High School office 507-362-4431. (The Morristown office is under construction.) #WEMBucs

WEM Softball is proud to host the 2020 Senior Salute - Gopher vs Valley Conference Softball game!!! It's an opportunity for players to play one last game in their high school uniform. WEM's Trista Hering will be participating! We are proud to honor and salute these 2020 seniors who had to endure personal sacrifices this spring for the health and safety of our communities! They did so with grace and class and it is our pleasure to pay tribute to them in the Senior Salute game! Spectators must follow MN COVID-19 mandates and protocols for social distancing.

post_text: We know everyone is wondering how school will look in 2020-21. We have been directed by the Minnesota Department of Education (MDE) to develop three plans for the start of school this fall. The plans will include face-to-face instruction, a hybrid (bringing in fewer students while delivering distance learning to others), and distance learning. We will be notified the week of July 27th on which plan we are to use for the start of school. Each plan will include safety protocols for staff and students based on current health guidelines. In the meantime, we have been collecting input from WEM parents and staff via online surveys to ensure everyone has a chance to be heard. Our priorities remain on student and staff safety and support. Click below for MDE family resources. #WEMBucs
shared_text:
EDUCATION.MN.GOV
Supporting Students and Families COVID-19 Resources
text:
We know everyone is wondering how school will look in 2020-21. We have been directed by the Minnesota Department of Education (MDE) to develop three plans for the start of school this fall. The plans will include face-to-face instruction, a hybrid (bringing in fewer students while delivering distance learning to others), and distance learning. We will be notified the week of July 27th on which plan we are to use for the start of school. Each plan will include safety protocols for staff and students based on current health guidelines. In the meantime, we have been collecting input from WEM parents and staff via online surveys to ensure everyone has a chance to be heard. Our priorities remain on student and staff safety and support. Click below for MDE family resources. #WEMBucs

EDUCATION.MN.GOV
Supporting Students and Families COVID-19 Resources

post_text: With the scary things going on in our world and right here in Minnesota, remember to take care of yourself and each other. Be kind. It's easy, free, and important. #mentalhealthawarenessmonth #bekind
shared_text:
Stomp Out Bullying
May 27 at 8:47 PM ·

Being kind to others and kind to ourselves is vital for our mental health and, the amazing thing is, that there’s potential for kindness every single day in everything we do.
#MentalHealthAwarenessMonth
text:
With the scary things going on in our world and right here in Minnesota, remember to take care of yourself and each other. Be kind. It's easy, free, and important. #mentalhealthawarenessmonth #bekind

Stomp Out Bullying
May 27 at 8:47 PM ·

Being kind to others and kind to ourselves is vital for our mental health and, the amazing thing is, that there’s potential for kindness every single day in everything we do.
#MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

May 22 at 4:32 PM ·

WEM Graduation on May 22, 2020 was an experiment and a labor of love by many people working together to honor the Class of 2020 in the best ways possible under unfortunate circumstances. Due to the global pandemic of COVID-19 a.k.a Coronavirus, the final two months of the school year were conducted via distance learning, and the traditional graduation ceremony was not allowed, We had seniors in vehicles with their parents/guardians in a parade from Morristown to Elysian to Waterville. Grads then crossed a stage for their diploma and a photo.

The stage area was blocked off from extended family and friends. To assure social distancing and crowds of less than 10 as per Governor Tim Walz,…

shared_text:
Waterville-Elysian-Morristown Schools added 39 new photos — at Waterville-Elysian-Morristown Schools.
May 14 at 5:01 PM · Waterville, MN ·

Under Executive Orders from Governor Tim Walz, Minnesota is social distancing and prohibited from having large gatherings that could facilitate the spread of COVID-19. So WEM held a drive-through for students to return school materials after weeks of distance learning at the end of the school year. A special time was set for seniors to return their items, receive awards announced the previous night at a virtual Night of Excellence, see their teachers and friends, and ride in a parade on the street between the school and the football field. Everyone had a great time, and it was a beautiful day! Congratulations, Class of 2020!

Watch the videos on the NFHS Network website.

Senior Parade: https://www.nfhsnetwork.com/events/watervilleelysianmorristown-high-school-waterville-mn/evt9f3bed09dc

Night of Excellence:
https://www.nfhsnetwork.com/events/watervilleelysianmorristown-high-school-waterville-mn/evt74e5688641

post_text:
It's WEM Bike to ______Day! As an alternative to “Bike to School Day” please join us for Bike to ____ Day at WEM. Choose your own adventure to celebrate biking and fill in that blank! Please share your biking pictures in the comment section of this post.

Although we can't get together in person for large-scale events like "Bike to School Day," we encourage students and families to get outside on a walk or bike ride when possible. Biking is not only great exercise. Studies have shown that physical exercise stimulates brain activity and is conducive to learning. Plus, it’s a fun and easy way to help children get their recommended 60 minutes of physical activity per day. #BikeToSchoolDay

post_text: May 1, 2020 is School Lunch Hero Day! Our WEM school lunch staff members prepare healthy meals, adhere to strict nutrition standards, navigate food allergies, and offer service with a smile. During the global pandemic and distance learning, these are the "essential workers" making sure all students in need within our community get daily breakfast and lunch for free. School lunch professionals are true heroes! THANK YOU! #WEMBucs #SchoolLunchHeroDay

post_text: The 5th graders are beginning STEM Sports for Science class. This is a fun way to wrap up the year. The first sport was basketball. Students were told to build a catapult (with the materials listed and provided to them) that will launch a ping pong ball into a hoop/basket that is 150 cm away with as much accuracy as possible. Here are a few of the catapult designs. (On Monday, the three 5th grade teachers delivered project materials to all their students, including popsicle sticks, masking tape, straws, pipe cleaners, etc.), #WEMBucs #STEM

post_text:
April 19-25 is National Volunteer Week. One way to get involved is with the Homemade Mask Drive launched by the Governor and Lieutenant Governor. On Saturday, April 25 from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m., Minnesotans can deliver homemade masks to their local fire station. Fire stations will then deliver the masks to local congregate living facilities for their employees and residents to wear. All 775 fire departments in the State of Minnesota will participate. The website offers mask design guides and patterns.
https://mn.gov/covid19/for-minnesotans/volunteer/masks.jsp

post_text: WEM families, here is an update from our local public libraries, including Elysian and Waterville. Be sure to check into their many online resources, including e-books and arts & crafts classes through Creative Bug. If you don't have a library card, contact the library, and they will hook you up.
shared_text:
Elysian Area Library & Heritage Center
April 14 at 9:37 AM ·

Hello Library Friends,
We will be following the Stay Home MN and the Elysian Library will remain CLOSED through Monday, May 4. There will not be curbside pickup/delivery available. Please see the attached photo for further details. We miss you all and know how hard this is. It's hard for us too. We can't wait to continue to share books and talk books with you. We are grateful that our library board continues to consider the health of our staff and patrons while making this difficult decision.
text:
WEM families, here is an update from our local public libraries, including Elysian and Waterville. Be sure to check into their many online resources, including e-books and arts & crafts classes through Creative Bug. If you don't have a library card, contact the library, and they will hook you up.

Elysian Area Library & Heritage Center
April 14 at 9:37 AM ·

Hello Library Friends,
We will be following the Stay Home MN and the Elysian Library will remain CLOSED through Monday, May 4. There will not be curbside pickup/delivery available. Please see the attached photo for further details. We miss you all and know how hard this is. It's hard for us too. We can't wait to continue to share books and talk books with you. We are grateful that our library board continues to consider the health of our staff and patrons while making this difficult decision.

post_text: We are so proud of you, WEM families! As we kick off week two of distance learning, here’s something to ponder. “We need to make friends with ourselves. We are stuck with our self all day, so let’s be kinder, gentler, more amusing company. Let’s take our own hand and say, ‘...You’re doing a good job. I’m proud of how you’re handling all this craziness....Don’t give up. Carry on, warrior.’” Glennon Doyle Melton, Author #MotivationalMonday

post_text: Le Sueur County Public Health has asked WEM to share the update that there is a new phone line to assist Le Sueur County residents who are under isolation/quarantine or are highly susceptible to COVID-19. The purpose is to assist individuals in meeting essential needs (food, medications) if they do not have family, friends, or neighbors to assist them during this time. Please share this with anyone you know who may benefit from this assistance. Call 507-357-8396 Monday through Friday from 10:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

On the WEM Facebook page we try not to support or advertise any one business, however, as we begin Distance Learning we would like every family to have internet service.

So, if you do not have internet access at home give Midco a call. Midco is introducing an all-new package, Midco Internet Basic for households with K-12 and/or college students who don’t have internet access.
• Education Assistance Credit makes the service FREE through June 15, 20201
• Speeds up to 25 Mbps download and 3 Mbps upload
• Standard or wireless modem included
Starting now, qualified households can begin enrolling.

This is ONLY for people who do NOT currently have internet access.

For more information call 1.833.338.4638 or 1-800-888-1300.

We have called Midco and this seems to be legitimate. Please share this information with anyone you know who has school age children and no internet access.

https://drive.google.com/a/wem.k12.mn.us/file/d/1IrtpPIVfnDSkuyXj9mlkXJXcZ1lxV-wu/view?usp=sharing

post_text:
Hello, WEM parents and students. This is a reminder that today, Thursday, March 26, 2020, is the last day to clear out your lockers and pick up any materials that your teacher may have left for you.

Distance Learning begins Monday, March 30.

Beginning tomorrow night, Minnesotans are being asked to "Shelter in Place,” and our Distance Learning Plan goes into effect on March 30. That means that Monday is a school day, and you should be checking in with your teacher online or looking at the materials that were provided to you.

Please get what you need by 7:00 p.m. so you can be ready for Distance Learning!

Stay home. Be safe.
"We will get through this.”
shared_text:
THU, MAR 26
CoVID-19 Student/Family Item Pick-Up
